  "abstract": "Pigeonpea is diploid (2n = 22) and primarily grown for food (dry seeds or green vegetables)\r\n• Sixth most important food legume crop and good source of protein; enriches soil; provides fodder and fuel wood; and arrests soil erosion\r\n• Grown in over 82 countries worldwide as a field and/or backyard crop\r\n• As a regular crop, grown only in 19 countries on 4.6 million ha producing 3.5 million tons of grain (FAOSTAT, 2005).......................",
